      "explanation": "冊 (satsu) is the counter for bound things like books, so 三冊 (san-satsu) means “three books.” 本が三冊あります (hon ga san-satsu arimasu) puts the noun first, then the number with its counter, then the existence verb.",
      "sentence": "本が三冊あります",
      "translation": "There are three books"
